cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a strategy for managing interference among D2D links in cellular networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the optimization of cluster size and bandwidth allocation, which involves information theory concepts such as channel capacity and coding theory. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The caching policy proposed in the paper involves exploiting the caching capability at the users, which can be seen as a social network aspect. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The proposed strategy involves dividing D2D users into clusters, which can be seen as a distributed computing aspect. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the impact of content popularity distribution on the performance of the proposed strategy, which is related to multimedia content delivery.
